\c 6
\s1 Woe to the Complacent
\m 
\v 1 Alas \add for\add* those being at ease in Zion, and those who feel secure on Mount Samaria, the notables of the best of the nations! The house of Israel resorts to them. 
\v 2 Cross over \add to\add* Calneh and see, and go from there \add to\add* Hamath Rabbah and go down \add to\add* Gath of the Philistines. \add Are\add* you better than these kingdoms, or is their territory greater than your territory? 
\v 3 You that put off the day of disaster and bring near a reign of violence! 
\v 4 \add Alas for\add* those who lie on beds of ivory and lounge on their couches, and those eating young rams from \add the\add* sheep and goats, and bull-calves from the middle of \add the\add* animal stall. 
\v 5 \add Alas for those\add* who sing to the tune of the harp; like David they improvise on instruments of music. 
\v 6 \add Alas for those\add* who drink from sprinkling bowls of wine and anoint themselves with the best of olive oils and are not grieved over the ruin of Joseph. 
\v 7 Therefore, they shall now go into exile at the head of the exiles and the feast of lounging shall pass away.
\s1 Yahweh Abhors Israel’s Pride
\m 
\v 8 My Lord Yahweh has sworn by himself, ⸤declares⸥\f + \fr 6:8 \ft Literally “a declaration of” \f* Yahweh, the God of hosts: “I abhor the pride of Jacob and I hate his citadel fortresses and I will deliver \add the\add* city and its fullness!” 
\v 9 And then if ten people remain in one house, they too will die. 
\v 10 And \add if\add* one’s relative, who burns \add the body\add*, lifts it up and brings the body out of the house and he will say to someone in the innermost part of the house, “\add Are there\add* any more with you?” and he will say, “None,” then he will say, “Silence,” because \add we\add* must not invoke the name of Yahweh. 
\v 11 Look, Yahweh \add is\add* going to command and the great house will be destroyed \add to\add* bits and the little house \add to\add* pieces. 
\v 12 Do horses run on rocks, or does one plow the sea with oxen?\f + \fr 6:12 \ft Or “does one plow them with oxen” \f* But you have turned justice into poison and \add the\add* fruit of righteousness into wormwood! 
\v 13 \add You\add* who rejoice over Lo-Debar, who say, “Have we not taken Karnaim for ourselves by our strength?” 
\v 14 Indeed, I \add am\add* going to raise up against you a nation, O house of Israel, ⸤declares⸥\f + \fr 6:14 \ft Literally “a declaration of” \f* Yahweh, the God of hosts. And they shall oppress you from Lebo-hamath up to the wadi of the Arabah.
\c 7
\s1 Warning Visions
\m 
\v 1 This is what my Lord Yahweh showed me, and look, \add he\add* is going to form locusts at the beginning of the sprouting of the second crop, and look, after the mowings of the king. 
\v 2 And then when they\f + \fr 7:2 \ft Hebrew “he/it” \f* finished eating the vegetation of the land, I said, “O Lord Yahweh, please forgive! How can Jacob stand, because he \add is\add* small?” 
\v 3 Yahweh relented concerning this. “It will not be,” said Yahweh. 
\v 4 This is what my Lord Yahweh showed me, and look, my Lord Yahweh was going to call for a legal case with fire, and it devoured the great deep and it ate up the plots of ground. 
