\v 8 And Yahweh said to me, “What do you see?” And I said, “A plummet.” And my Lord said, “Look, I \add am\add* going to set a plummet in the midst of my people, Israel. I will not pass them by again. 
\v 9 The high places of Isaac shall become desolate and the sanctuaries of Israel shall be laid waste. And I will rise against the house of Jeroboam with the sword.”
\s1 Amaziah’s Opposition
\m 
\v 10 Then Amaziah the priest of Bethel sent to Jeroboam the king of Israel, saying, “Amos has conspired against you in the midst of the house of Israel. The land is not able to endure all of his words. 
\v 11 For this Amos has said, ‘Jeroboam will die by the sword and Israel will certainly go into exile \add away\add* from his land.’ ” 
\v 12 And Amaziah said to Amos, “\add O\add* seer, go, flee to the land of Judah and earn food there and prophesy there!” 
\v 13 But do not prophesy again at Bethel, because this \add is\add* a sanctuary of a king and this \add is\add* a temple of a kingdom.” 
\v 14 And Amos answered and said to Amaziah, “I am not a prophet and I \add am\add* not a son of a prophet, but I \add am\add* a herdsman and I am one taking care of sycamore trees. 
\v 15 And Yahweh took me from \add following\add* behind the sheep and goats and Yahweh said to me, “Go, prophesy to my people Israel! 
\v 16 And so then, hear the word of Yahweh! You are saying, ‘You must not prophesy against Israel and you must not preach against the house of Isaac!’ 
\v 17 Therefore, thus says Yahweh, ‘Your wife will become a prostitute in the city and your sons and your daughters will fall by the sword and your land will be divided with a line, and you\f + \fr 7:17 \ft Emphatic second person pronoun \f* will die in an unclean land and Israel will surely go into exile from this land.’ ”
\c 8
\s1 A Basket of Ripe Fruit
\m 
\v 1 My Lord Yahweh showed me this, and there was a basket of summer fruit. 
\v 2 And he said, “What do you see, Amos?” And I said, “A basket of summer fruit.” And Yahweh said to me, “The end has come upon my people Israel. I will not pass by them again!” 
\v 3 “And the songs of the temple shall become wailings in that day,” ⸤declares⸥\f + \fr 8:3 \ft Literally “a declaration of” \f* my Lord Yahweh. “The corpses are numerous; he throws them in every place. Be quiet!” 
\v 4 Hear this, those who trample on \add the\add* poor and who annihilate the afflicted of \add the\add* land, 
\v 5 saying, “When will the new moon be over, so that we can sell grain? And the Sabbath, so that we can open the grain bins, that we can make \add the\add* ephah small and make \add the\add* shekel large, and can practice deceit \add with\add* a set of scales of deceit? 
