\v 11 Look, the days are coming,” ⸤declares⸥\f + \fr 8:11 \ft Literally “a declaration of” \f* my Lord Yahweh, “when I will send a famine in the land, not a famine for bread and not a thirst for water, but ⸤of hearing⸥\f + \fr 8:11 \ft Literally “but if to hear” \f* the words of Yahweh! 
\v 12 And they will wander from sea to sea and from \add the\add* north and to \add the\add* east. They will roam about to seek the word of Yahweh, but they will not find \add it\add*! 
\v 13 In that day the beautiful young women and the young men will faint because of thirst. 
\v 14 \add These are\add* those who swear by the guilt of Samaria and say, ‘By the life of your gods, O Dan,’ and ‘By the life of the way of Beersheba,’ they will fall and they will not rise again.”
\c 9
\s1 Destruction of Israel
\m 
\v 1 I saw my Lord standing by the altar and he said, “Strike the capitals so that the thresholds will shake, and shatter them on the head of all of them, and I will kill the rest of them with the sword. A fugitive belonging to them will not run away, and a survivor belonging to them will not escape. 
\v 2 If they dig into Sheol, from there my hand will take them, and \add even\add* if they climb up \add to\add* heaven, from there I will bring them down. 
\v 3 And \add even\add* if they hide themselves on the top of Carmel, from there I will search and will take them, and \add even\add* if they hide from before my eyes at the bottom of the sea, from there I will command the sea serpent and it will bite them. 
\v 4 And \add even\add* if they go into captivity before their enemies, from there I will command the sword and it will kill them, and I will fix my eyes on them for harm and not for good.” 
\v 5 And \add thus will do\add* the Lord Yahweh of hosts, who touches the earth and it melts, and all of those living in it mourn, and all of it rises like the Nile and it sinks down like \add the\add* Nile of Egypt, 
\v 6 who builds his upper chambers in the heavens and lays the foundation of his vault on the earth, who calls for the waters of the sea and pours them on the surface of the earth—Yahweh is his name. 
\v 7 “Are you not like the Cushites to me, O people of Israel?” ⸤declares⸥\f + \fr 9:7 \ft Literally “a declaration of” \f* Yahweh. “Did I not bring up Israel from the land of Egypt and \add the\add* Philistines from Caphtor and ⸤the Arameans⸥\f + \fr 9:7 \ft Literally “Aram” \f* from Kir? 
